Loot Table
1. ModBlockLootTableProvider
    * Line 30 - Block Drops Itself
    * Line 34 - Block Drops 1 Ore
    * Line 38 - Block Drops Random Amount
2. ModBlockTagsProvider
    * Line 19 - The Block Can Actually Be Mined
    * Line 27 and 30 Controls Tier of Tool Needed to Mine the Block


Crafting Recipe
1. ModRecipeProvider
    * Line 35 - List all Blocks/Items able to be Smelted/Blasted
    * Line 40 - Can Edit Smelting Time/XP/Product
    * line 43 - Same as Smelting but Blasting
    * Line 52 - Shapeless Recipes
    * Line 63 - Turn Block into 9 Items
    * Line 72 - WARNING: If Multiple Recipe Have the Same output, id: Tag is Required to Differentiate between them
            * Use Shaped() Instead of Shapeless() for Specific Positions, Because Shapeless Ignores Spaces while Shaped Doesn't
            * Must Define Multiple Letters (Line 56) for a Multi-Item Crafting Recipe

Custom Items
1. Add New Java Class to custom Folder
    * Experiments Mostly
        * Click "Item" and then CRTL+H to See all Minecraft Items and how they Work
        * Type "override" to see More Options for Item Interactions
2. ModItems
    * Line 21 - Added New Item and Gave it the Durability Property
3. Creative Tab
    * Line 24 - Added the Item to the Creative Mode Tab
4. ModModelProvider
    * Line 34 - Added the Model as Well as Changed to "Hand Held Item"?
5. Add In Game name and PNG for Texture
6. Datagen

Custom Block
1. Add New Java Class to custom Folder
    * Experiments Mostly
        * Click "Block" and then CRTL+H to See all Minecraft Blocks and how they Work
        * Type "override" to see More Options for Item Interactions
2. Add to
    * ModBlocks - Basic Settings for the Block
    * ModCreativeModeTab
    * ModBlocksLootTable - What Loot It Drops
    * ModBlockTagsProvider - How it Can Be Mined
    * ModModelProvider - Block Model when it is in Hand
    * en_us.json - Renames Block In-Game
    * Texture - How the Block Looks




Notes
* CRTL + D: short cut to copy and pasting a whole line instantly
* Middle Mouse Button or CRT+Left Click to go to file where function is used
    * Used to pull up Minecraft files usually
* Click "Item" or "Block", then CRTL+H to See all Minecraft Items/Blocks and how they Work
* Type "override" to see More Options for Item Interactions
* If any new additions dont show up in game, check Build Folder
  to make sure DataGen ran correctly

Github
    * Update - Get other peoples changes
    * Commit - Save my changes locally
    * Push - Upload committed changes to Github

    Branches - Alternate Code So You Can Work Without Affecting Main Code
        * Checkout - Switch to a different branch or revision
        * Merge - Combine changes from one branch into another
        * Rebase - Move your branch on top of another branch to create cleaner linear history
        * Revision - A Specific Saved Version of the Project